During training, the optimisation layer is run periodically to update the safe envelope. The MARL agents interact with the simulator, collecting trajectories. The centralised critic is trained on these trajectories using the full state information. During execution (or evaluation), the distributed control layer directly applies the learned policies, with occasional interventions from the optimisation layer if the safe envelope is updated.

